SEMIFINAL: PIOTR GŁOGOWSKI VS. MAGNUS LANTTO
============================================



 Posted in [GRAND PRIX MILAN 2015](/en/events/coverage/gpmil15)
 on December 14, 2014 






![](https://media.magic.wizards.com/styles/auth_small/public/images/person/henke_author.jpg)
By Tobi Henke











Two little-known players met in this semifinal pairing, two players still looking to make a name for themselves. One of them would have further opportunity by advancing to the finals of this 1,760-player event!



Magnus Lantto was playing [Birthing Pod](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Birthing+Pod); Piotr Głogowski had brought an [Amulet of Vigor](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Amulet+of+Vigor)/Primeval Titan/Hive Mind concoction with [Summer Bloom](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Summer+Bloom), [Azusa, Lost but Seeking](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azusa%2C+Lost+but+Seeking), and lots of bouncelands like [Simic Growth Chamber](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Simic+Growth+Chamber). This would certainly make for an interesting match!



Game 1
======



Głogowski only cast his first spells on turn three: [Summoner's Pact](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Summoner%27s+Pact) followed by [Azusa, Lost but Seeking](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azusa%2C+Lost+but+Seeking). He then spend turn four paying for the pact.



Meanwhile, Lantto had summoned some creatures, stuffed those creatures into [Birthing Pod](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Birthing+Pod) to get bigger creatures, but all of that proved immaterial when, on turn five, Głogowski cast [Hive Mind](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive+Mind) and two [Summoner's Pact](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Summoner%27s+Pact)s Lantto couldn't pay for.



Piotr Głogowski 1-0 Magnus Lantto


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Game 2
======



This time, Lantto started with some disruption. A turn-one [Thoughtseize](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thoughtseize) took [Primeval Titan](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Primeval+Titan) out of Głogowski's hand, and basically that was enough already. Lantto assembled some creatures, pointed a timely [Abrupt Decay](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Abrupt+Decay) at Głogowski's [Seal of Primordium](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seal+of+Primordium), and began using his [Birthing Pod](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Birthing+Pod), while Głogowski had a lot of mana but nothing to do with it.



And that didn't change until [Siege Rhino](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Siege+Rhino)s had decreased Głogowski life to 0 either.



Piotr Głogowski 1-1 Magnus Lantto



Game 3
======



Again, Lantto had [Thoughtseize](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thoughtseize) and decided to pick Głogowski's only real business spell in [Summoner's Pact](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Summoner%27s+Pact). By turn three, Głogowski had access to six mana and again nothing to spend it on.


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Or at least that's what it looked like. In fact, Głogowski was hiding [Hive Mind](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive+Mind) in his hand and was just waiting for a lethal combination of Pacts. He wasn't hiding it very well though, because Lantto found it with [Thoughtseize](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thoughtseize). Głogowski decided to store another [Hive Mind](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive+Mind) on the battlefield, but lost that to [Reclamation](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reclamation) Sage instead.



In the meantime, aggressive Podding had taken Lantto to 3 and there was a momentary scare when Głogowski attacked with a 0/1 Plant token provided by [Khalni Garden](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Khalni+Garden) and pumped by [Slay](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Slay)ers' Stronghold. But that only put Lantto at 1 and he quickly went back to 8, casting [Kitchen Finks](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kitchen+Finks) and turning that into [Siege Rhino](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Siege+Rhino). His creatures overran Głogowski soon after.



**Piotr Głogowski 1-2 Magnus Lantto**
